steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"eku5s","text":"mRNA was purified from 1 μg of total RNA using oligo(dT)-attached mRNA capture magnetic beads (Vazyme, cat#401) following the user manual. The final purified mRNA was dissolved in 10.5 μl ddH2O.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":191,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"af4gq","text":"Second-strand cDNA was synthesized by adding 10 μl 5 x second strand buffer, 1 μl dUTP-containing dNTP mix (20 mM dUTP, 10 mM each dATP, dGTP, and dCTP), 1 μl E. coli DNA ligase, 2 μl DNA polymerase I, 0.06 μl RNase H, and 15.94 μl ddH2O to adjust the reaction volume to 50 μl. The solution was incubated at 16 °C for 1 h.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"37ui4","text":"The resulting double-stranded cDNA from previous step was tagmented by adding 20 μl 5x Tn5 Tagmentation Buffer,16 μl 50% PEG 8000, 2 pmol(0.5 μl) Tn5 transposase, and 14 μl ddH2O to adjust the reaction volume to 100 μl. The tagmentation reaction was performed at 55°C for 10 min, after which 10 μl 0.2% SDS was added and the enzyme deactivated by heating to 85°C for 5 min. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1d6jq","text":"For first-strand cDNA synthesis, mRNA was reverse transcribed in a PCR tube with the following setup:10 μl purified mRNA, 1 μl 50 μM Oligo (dT)23VN, 1 μl 50 μM random primers, 4 μl 5 × HiScript III Buffer, 0.5 μl dNTP Mix (10 mM each dATP, dTTP, dGTP, and dCTP), 1 μl 40 U/μl Recombinant RNasin® Ribonuclease Inhibitor, 1 μl 200 U/μl Hiscript III Reverse Transcriptase, 1 μl 120 ng/μl actinomycin D, and ddH2O as needed to adjust the reaction volume to 20 μl. The reverse transcription was performed under the following program: using a heated lid, 25°C for 5 min, 55°C for 45 min, and finally 85°C for 5 min for deactivation. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":407,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e86j0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1d6jq","text":"Set up the following reaction in a 1.5 mL centrifuge tube: 5 μL of Tn5 transposase (10 pmol/μL), 1.2 μL of adaptor mix (50 pmol/μL), 6.3 μL of coupling buffer (included in the commerical Tn5 products). Pipette 20 times gently to mix well and incubate at 30°C in a water bath for 1 h. The final concentration of transposase = 4 pmol/ μL. Store at -20°C until use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7ms55","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9k3l6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e86j0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"e2539","text":"Molar ratio of adaptor mix: transposase =1.2:1.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1d6jq","text":"Dilute oligos (Primer A, Primer B, and dU-Primer C, refer to Table S1) to 100 μM concentration using the annealing buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1d6jq","text":"Set up the following two reactions in PCR tubes: Reaction 1 (adaptor AB), 10 μL of 100 μM primer A, 10 μL of 100 μM primer B; Reaction 2 (adaptor AC), 10 μL of 100 μM primer A, 10 of μL 100 μM primer C.Anneal the adapters in the PCR machine using the following program: heat lid (102°C), 75°C for 15 min, 60°C for 10 min, 50°C for 10 min, 40°C for 10 min, 25°C for 30 min.Combine adaptor AB and adaptor AC at 1:1 ratio, designated as“adaptor mix”. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fv14j","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"du1m6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e86j0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"4m5pu","text":"The adapters are partially double-stranded DNA molecules (concentration = 50 pmol/μL)","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9ot0n","text":"Add 100 μHieff NGS® Smarter DNA Clean Beadsto the tagmentation products, purified the DNA following the user guide.Dissolvethe resulting DNA in 20 μl ddH2O. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":153,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8q9nj","text":"Preparation for PCR amplification was then carried out by mixing the 20 μl of eluted DNA with 25 μl 2x Phanta® Max buffer, 2 μl dNTP Mix (10 mM each dATP, dTTP, dGTP, and dCTP), and 1 μl Bst 2.0, and extension was performed at 72°C for 20 min followed by deactivation at 85°C for 20 min. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"37j5d","text":"Add 1.5 μl Heat-labile UDG (1 U/μl), 1 μl Phanta® Max Super-Fidelity DNA Polymerase, 1 μl primer N50X (20 μM), and 1 μl primer N70X (20 μM)to the PCR tube, and PCR was performed according to the following program: 25 °C for 20 min; 95 °C for 3 min; 14 cycles of 95 °C for 30 s, 60 °C for 30 s, and 72 °C for 30 s; 72 °C for 5 min; 4 °C for 1 min. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"21qgd","text":"Take3 μl of the PCR productfor agarose gel electrophoresis to determine the concentration and size distribution of bulk DNA products.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b9skf","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"8rjs6","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"e4tf8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"6d13t","text":"An additional 1-2 PCR cycles were carried out if necessary until the DNA bands were visible on agarose gel. ","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}},"1":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"A40FB0707D0A11ED9D04D193DF114393","height":416,"id":328231,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"图片 1.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/katjbmx2x.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/kathbmx2x.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/katibmx2x.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/katgbmx2x.webp","width":287}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6ss64","text":"The PCR products were purified using 60 μl (1.2 volume) Hieff NGS® Smarter DNA Clean Beads (Yeasen) following the user guide, and the resulting library was dissolved in 30 μl ddH2O for further quality control (QC) and NGS sequencing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":178,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
